wikipedia_page.main: William Western Knatchbull-Hugessen (23 May 1837 – 6 September 1864) was an English amateur cricketer who played in three first-class cricket matches in 1858 and 1859.

response: The house was built in 1342 for Lucas of Vienne, the Chief Archer to Edward, the Black Prince. It was altered and extended between the 15th and the 19th centuries, with James Huguesson buying the property in 1633. The house remained in the Huguesson and Knatchbull-Hugessen families for over 300 years. Sir Edward Knatchbull, 9th Baronet inherited it from Dorothea Hugessen, who had married naturalist Joseph Banks but died childless, and the estate was farmed by William Knatchbull-Hugessen in the 1860s.The History of Provender House, Provender House website.
